<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100200416520343></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100200416520343><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100200416520343>RE: Race...?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100200416520343#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=65654><span id= >shoedaman</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>26 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 2nd 2:29 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.37]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The best race is basically the race that you want to play.&nbsp;&nbsp;They all have their ups and downs and we could trash each and every one of them until were blue in the face.  My personal preference is the Iksar due to the regen,  starting zone, and exp bonus from kunark zones.  The regen helps alot believe it or not.  Every little bit of regen makes a difference when medding for health.  The starting zone is FOB,  it has lots of bone chips for our pet summons.  Kurn's tower is right there in the zone and you can pretty much level all the way to level 20 in this zone alone if you wanted to.  Then you have the Lake of Ill Omen to go to around 15 and up if you like and get great exp there as well as plenty more bone chips for pet.  Great groups there.  Iksars have bad faction most places but you just have to work on it.  If your worried about being KOS or faction problems,  then try human or erudite necro instead.  You just have to deal with the no night vision thing.  There are plenty of items around to correct your night vision.  Necros are intelligence casters so the more int you have the more mana you have.  Erudites have the highest starting int.  Dark elves have great night vision.  I don't know much about gnomes,  never played one but I'm sure they have their own ups and downs as well.  Just play a class that you will feel comfortable with and that you like the way it looks or acts or the starting area or whatever.  Theres not really a best class,  the player makes the class not the race.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
