	   <tr><td colspan=2>Encyclopidia Necrotheurgia is dropped of Ashenbone Broodmaster in Hate on the second floor. It will summon a pet that hits 2 harder has more hp and is taller also seems to hit faster. For example my monk pet will hit for 61 and kick for 71 without book max pet is 59 hit. One more misconception about post 50 necro is that soloing ends at lvl 52 or so, LMAO NOT! I have soloed all the way to 59 and am continuing through to 60. Skyfire is great for post 50 till about 54, then ditch the pet and root dot for twice the exp.&nbsp;&nbsp;Skyfire can be done until lvl 57 quite efficiently. (Holgresh elder beads help greatly with downtime) After that Howling Stones zone in is insane exp through to 60. Now about raiding, Necros are both needed and though our job changes from Dmg dealers to mana whores it is a job none the less. One more misconception is that our pets are not allowed on high lvl raids. FALSE I am in one of the most powerful guilds in EQ and we use pets for almost ever high lvl encounter (non dungeon) I have played the high lvl game with 3 classes and necro is by far still the most fun. Besides raiding for farming a focused Spec pet is about all ya need to just park him and go afk while he solos room full of mobs. There is just something about NEVER needing a group and being able to farm stuff no other class can its kinda nice to only group when you want too.<br><br><br>Dameont LilGrim (Rising Ascension)<br>59 Necromancer of Povar<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
