<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100029465843370></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100029465843370><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100029465843370>New patch changed unarmed combat?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=14&mid=100029465843370#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Sep 12th 7:37 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm a 25th level necro. Got my 25 ding yesterday after the patch when I gained about 1 yellow bub in less than 45 minutes. Some of that was with a friend, but a good chunk of it was on my own fighting through yellow skellies and gobbies as if they were BUTTER!<br><br>The patch seems to have made my unarmed pet (fighting with Monk unarmed combat code, perhaps) MUCH more deadly. This may be a bug, but there's no way I can be sure, and I can assure you I'm not going to fight without my pet just to avoid "abusing" a bug.<br><br>Even without the patch, though, here's a strategy that's working well for me in terms of exp, and plat looted from dead:<br><br>1. Go to LOIO, on NW side of lake so that you are between gobbie fort and sarnak fort, but on shoreline. This is a good place at 24, maybe 23, definitely at 25!<br>2. Put pet on guard duty. Bring up Banshee and Shield. Go out onto the plain between the two forts and find something white or blue to start (yellow was hard before patch, but doable if you're careful). Put Leech on it, and run back to pet.<br>3. Sick pet on target while you dump HF, SV, SoP. <br>4. After SoP, mob should start attacking you. Start meele with mob (you don't expect to do much damage, just give it a target, and let Banshee do its word while leech protects you hp).<br>5. While being attacked, you will want to re-cast leech and, depending on mob strength and what your life is doing, get off 0-2 taps to recover HP.<br>6. Once mob is dead or running, cast allure and med 'til you're up to full.<br>7. Repeat.<br><br>I find that downtime is annoying this way, but I can take on yellow and white pretty easily which means I'm gaining as much as 1/4-1/2 blue per kill!<br><br>With Allure, I end up getting back to full within 30-60 sec.<br><br>With a partner, I don't modify this much. The only thing I do is drop the Banshee and instead bring up subversion or compact to help my partner.<br><br>My downtime yesterday while I had just one partner was something like 20 sec per 2-3 kills. I was NEVER taking down allure and I was making an average of about 5gp per kill (after split).<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
